    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="poem" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" rhyme="aa"><!-- this poem never coded from ms.; text is from 1903; compare against ms carefully -->
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l><handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="cursive" medium="ink"/>Oh, softly blew the morning breeze<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">810</add></l><!-- add remainder of JR line nos. -->
                <l>Through <placeName corresp="#CHIAVENNA">Chiavenna</placeName>'s myrtle trees,</l>
                <l>And oer the green hills viny spread</l> <!--got rid of two apostrophes-->
                <l>That rose in many a rounded head</l>
                <l>Beneath the <geogName corresp="#ALPS">Alpine</geogName> rocks of red</l>
                    <l>And the fresh snow had fallen that night,<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">815</add></l> 
                <l>And sprinkled with its mantle white</l>
                <l>The mountain amphitheatre</l>
                <l>That rose around us far and near</l>
                <l>Though in such far confusion hurled</l>
                    <l>They looked to rule oer all the world<add rend="linenumber-right-JR">820</add></l> 
                <l>And the white clouds seemed to immerse,</l>
                <l>Another ruin'd universe.</l>
                </lg>
           </div>
